                    <span>Adams' book is wonderful for learning the basics of suspension design.  More important than only learning the concepts of suspension geometry is the application of that into practical use, which Adams shows concisely.  His information is put out in a way that you can actually make a simple system, then understand the 'why' behind it enough to tune it.  Very good for anything less than professional design.</span>
                  
